title: Piling on? Ohio T-shirt company immortalizes Michigan fans' pain
text:
Piling on? Ohio T-shirt company immortalizes Michigan fans' pain FOX Sports 
Oct 19, 2015 at 5:18p ET + 
This fan was shocked by the way the Michigan-Michigan State game ended. ESPN Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 5:18p ET 
No rivalry is safe this week for Michigan . 
Losing on an incredible fumbled punt snap touchdown return to Michigan State over the weekend was obviously painful, but now a t-shirt company in Cincinnati has decided to pour some salt in the wounds. true 
The Depressed Michigan fan Tee is blowing up! Our store has received calls from Sports Illustrated praising it, as well... Posted by Cincy Shirts on Monday, October 19, 2015 
The image in the first 'O' mirrors that of shocked Michigan fans at Michigan Stadium after they saw the Spartans snatch victory from the jaws of defeat on Saturday. 
This is sure to be a big seller in the Buckeye State, and the seller -- Cincy Shirts -- noted in a Facebook post it has already caused a stir -- and drawn complaints from some folks in Maize and Blue.
